The paper deals with materialized view selection in data warehouses, which is a topic related to database management systems. Therefore, cs.DB is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a data mining technique (clustering) to determine clusters of similar queries, which falls under the scope of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of cost models to evaluate the cost of accessing data and storing views is related to optimization and decision-making, which are topics in data science (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed strategy in terms of query performance, which is a topic in information retrieval (cs.IR).
